  h1 Privacy Policy

  p This Privacy Policy hereby incorporates by reference all terms, conditions rules, policies and guidelines on the Site, including the Spongie Terms of Service (“Terms of Service”). This Privacy Policy is effective as of January 1, 2014. Your use or continued use of Spongie will signify your acceptance of this Privacy Policy. We reserve the right to modify the provisions in this Privacy Policy without prior notice to you, so please check back often for updates.

  p Spongie, LLC, ("Spongie", "us" or "we") respects the privacy of the visitors to its Web site, the home page of which is located at spongie.org ("Site"). This Privacy Policy is intended to inform you of our policies and practices regarding the collection, use and disclosure of Personal Information and by submitting Personal Information through the Site, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy and you expressly consent to the processing of your Personal Information according to this Privacy Policy. Your Personal Information may be processed by Spongie in the country where it was collected, as well as other countries (including the United States) where laws regarding processing of Personal Information may be less stringent than the laws in your country.

  .page-title Notification of Changes

  p We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time as Site Services change and expand. If we make substantial changes to this Privacy Policy, we will notify you of all significant changes by notice through the primary email address provided in your account information or via a prominent notice on our site.

  .page-title Information We Gather

  p When creating an account with Spongie, we will request the following information; name, email address, billing address and credit card information (for paid tier only) along with a unique username and password (generated by the user creating the account).

  p Spongie uses the collected information for the provision of products and services, billing, product improvements, identification, authentication, research and contact. Credit card information is transmitted via SSL ("Secure Socket Layer") encryption for your protection.

  .page-title Online Surveys

  p Occasionally, Spongie may conduct a User survey to collect information about our Users' preferences. These surveys are optional and if you choose to respond, your responses will be kept anonymous. None of this information is shared with third parties. The demographic information that Spongie collects in the registration process and through surveys is used to help us improve Site Services to meet the needs and preferences of our Users.

  .page-title Cookies

  p When you use the Site, Spongie may send small data files called cookies to your browser. Spongie uses cookies to enable Users to specify unique preferences and to track Visitor and User use of the site, including trends and patterns.

  .page-title How We Use and Disclose Information

  h4 Personal Information

  p We use Personal Information for our own internal purposes including contacting you via email to inform you about updates to Site Services and providing you with information relating to e-commerce transactions that you conduct on the Site. We reserve the right to disclose your information as required by law. We do not rent or sell our Users' Personal Information to third parties. We do, however, provide you with the opportunity to receive newsletters and other updates via email. If you decide to opt in to receive newsletters, you may opt out of receiving these newsletters at any time by clicking on “Unsubscribe to this Newsletter” at the bottom of any newsletter.

  h4 Legal Requests

  p Spongie cooperates with law enforcement inquiries, as well as other third parties to enforce laws, such as: intellectual property rights, fraud, theft, harassment and other rights. We can (and you authorize us to) disclose any information about you, including the content of your online communications, if we believe in good faith that such disclosure is necessary to (a) comply with relevant laws or to respond to subpoenas or warrants served on us; (b) protect or defend the rights or property of Spongie or third parties; (c) assist in an investigation; or (d) respond to an emergency that poses a threat to the safety of Users or other persons.

  h4 Anonymous Information

  p We may use Anonymous Information to analyze inquiry, request and usage patterns so that we may enhance our services and the Site. We reserve the right to use and disclose Anonymous Information to third parties in our discretion.

  h4 Comments Submitted by Users

  p Spongie wants to improve the quality of the services we provide and the User experience on the Site. We value your input and encourage you to help us expand and make improvements to the Site by providing us with any thoughts or comments you might have regarding our services or the operation of the Site. You can submit any comments via email to support@spongie.org. Your Username is optional. If you provide this information, we will only use it to acknowledge or respond to your comments. Submitting comments via email will not cause you to receive any secondary or promotional material, unless specifically requested by you. In certain circumstances, we may ask for your permission to post your comments in marketing or promotional materials.

  h4 Security

  p We will use commercially reasonable methods to keep Personal Information securely in our files and systems. Our Payment System is operated using secure Internet connections, using SSL (Secure Sockets Layer) encryption, to help protect your financial data. Please note that with current technology, we cannot guarantee the security of your data as it travels over the Internet. Refer to the “Security” agreement for more information.

  h4 Data Retention

  p We will retain your information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide you services. If you wish to cancel your account or request that we no longer use your information to provide you services please contact us. We will retain and use your information as necessary to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements.

  h4 Terminating Your Membership

  p We save your Personal Information until your membership with us is terminated and you unsubscribe to email notifications. To terminate your membership, contact us. If you terminate your membership, your Personal Information cannot be recovered. You may continue to receive email communications for a short period of time until we have updated all of our databases. After termination of your membership, your Personal Information may remain on our archived database and records. Notwithstanding the above, we will maintain information on Users who have been removed for violating our Membership Agreement.